The paper deals with wireless device-to-device (D2D) caching networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper proposes a cache-induced hierarchical cooperation scheme and associated cache content placement optimization algorithm, which involves designing a hierarchical structure for the network, and optimizing the placement of cache content. This involves aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as optimization (cs.SI).
